   "source": [
    "## Key Findings: London Borough Level Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Drilling down to borough level reveals significant intra-city variation in anxiety \n",
    "scores that country-level data completely obscures.\n",
    "\n",
    "All 32 boroughs show a similar pattern: declining anxiety 2011-2015, \n",
    "stabilising through to 2019, then a clear Covid spike in 2020 with varying \n",
    "intensity across boroughs. Post-2020 divergence is greater than pre-pandemic, \n",
    "suggesting uneven recovery across the city.\n",
    "\n",
    "This granularity supports the hypothesis that urban sub-geography matters — \n",
    "London is not a monolithic anxiety hotspot but a patchwork of distinct \n",
    "wellbeing profiles. Wealth, density, demographics and connectivity likely \n",
    "all play a role.\n",
    "\n",
    "Next step: identify consistently high and low anxiety boroughs, then overlay \n",
    "UK mobile subscription data as national context before moving to the Dash app build."
   ]
