   "source": [
    "## Highest and Lowest Anxiety Boroughs in London\n",
    "\n",
    "Highest anxiety boroughs (mean score 2011-2022):\n",
    "Southwark, Lambeth, Islington, Camden, Hackney\n",
    "\n",
    "Lowest anxiety boroughs (mean score 2011-2022):\n",
    "Brent, Barnet, Harrow, Newham, Enfield\n",
    "\n",
    "A striking pattern emerges: the highest anxiety boroughs are all \n",
    "inner-city, gentrified, high cost-of-living areas with large young \n",
    "professional populations. The lowest anxiety boroughs are outer London, \n",
    "more ethnically diverse, with stronger community structures and \n",
    "lower housing costs.\n",
    "\n",
    "This directly challenges the assumption that deprivation drives anxiety. \n",
    "Southwark and Camden are among London's most desirable and expensive areas. \n",
    "Newham and Enfield, historically more deprived, score lowest.\n",
    "\n",
    "Suggests cost of living pressure, social isolation, and the performative \n",
    "nature of urban professional life may be more significant anxiety drivers \n",
    "than poverty or lack of connectivity."
   ]
  },
