   "source": [
    "## Key Finding: Wellbeing Across All Measures\n",
    "\n",
    "The pattern is remarkably consistent across all four wellbeing measures.\n",
    "\n",
    "Newham and Enfield — the lowest anxiety boroughs — also score consistently \n",
    "well on happiness, life satisfaction, and worthwhile. They are not just \n",
    "less anxious, they appear genuinely more content across every dimension \n",
    "the ONS measures.\n",
    "\n",
    "Conversely, Southwark, Lambeth, Islington and Camden — the high anxiety \n",
    "boroughs — score lower on positive wellbeing measures too. Higher anxiety \n",
    "correlates with lower happiness and life satisfaction.\n",
    "\n",
    "This consistency across all four measures strengthens the finding. It is \n",
    "not a quirk of how anxiety is measured — it reflects a broader wellbeing \n",
    "gap between inner gentrified London and outer diverse London.\n",
    "\n",
    "The data quietly dismantles two assumptions: that deprivation drives poor \n",
    "mental health, and that living in \"cooler\", more culturally rich areas \n",
    "makes people happier. The opposite appears to be true.\n",
    "\n",
    "Possible drivers: community cohesion, cost of living pressure, social \n",
    "comparison, and the psychological weight of aspirational urban culture.\n",
    "\n",
    "Next step: overlay UK mobile subscription data, then move to building \n",
    "the Dash app."
